19:30.636 --> 19:33.639
Go ahead, Niles.
I know you were listening.

19:33.639 --> 19:35.641
Well...

19:35.641 --> 19:38.610
I wish you'd lent her your
Tennessee Williams biography.

19:38.610 --> 19:40.579
She wouldn't have kept
forgetting his name

19:40.579 --> 19:42.915
and calling him Indiana Jones.

19:47.052 --> 19:51.456
If it's any consolation,
I got fired from The Monocle.

19:53.325 --> 19:54.826
Oh, Niles, I'm sorry.

19:54.826 --> 19:56.094
Mm.

19:56.094 --> 19:57.896
I panned a wretched musical

19:57.896 --> 20:02.401
not realizing the lead was
the person who does Olga's hair.

20:02.401 --> 20:05.204
She fired you
just to placate her hairdresser?

20:05.204 --> 20:06.905
Electrolysist.

20:06.905 --> 20:08.774
And if you'd ever

20:08.774 --> 20:11.710
seen her in a sundress,
you'd forgive her as I have.

20:12.711 --> 20:14.680
Oh, I am sorry, Niles.

20:14.680 --> 20:16.215
Gosh, it's such
a shame, really.

20:16.215 --> 20:18.217
You know, I know how much
you loved that job

20:18.217 --> 20:20.586
and to lose it in such
an unceremonious fashion.

20:21.486 --> 20:23.488
Well, you know...

20:23.488 --> 20:25.958
I was thinking
of quitting that job anyway.

20:25.958 --> 20:27.893
Oh?
Mm-hmm.

20:27.893 --> 20:30.295
I felt I was
spreading myself too thin.

20:30.295 --> 20:32.564
Getting distracted
from my real work.

20:32.564 --> 20:33.865
I had the exact same thought.

20:33.865 --> 20:35.867
Even as I was preparing my show,
I thought,

20:35.867 --> 20:37.636
"Am I being fair
to my regular listeners?"

20:37.636 --> 20:38.737
They do depend on you.

20:38.737 --> 20:40.572
As do your patients.
Thank you.

20:40.572 --> 20:41.573
Gosh, you know,
is it any wonder

20:41.573 --> 20:43.976
we find ourselves
ex-critics?

20:43.976 --> 20:46.311
We were meant
to lose those jobs.

20:46.311 --> 20:47.779
It's as if
the Gods of psychiatry,

20:47.779 --> 20:48.780
jealous of our dalliance,

20:48.780 --> 20:51.149
have quietly stepped in
and put things right.

20:51.149 --> 20:52.484
Well put.

20:52.484 --> 20:53.919
Oh, thank you, thank you.

20:53.919 --> 20:55.954
You know, Niles,
if you're feeling a bit hungry,

20:55.954 --> 20:57.322
we could catch an early dinner
and then...

20:57.322 --> 21:00.125
Oh, oh, and then catch
the new Stoppard play. Splendid!

21:00.125 --> 21:01.560
You know,
it's just a shame

21:01.560 --> 21:04.563
my listeners never got to hear
my review of Streetcar.

21:04.563 --> 21:06.465
Oh, insightful,
was it? Groundbreaking.

21:06.465 --> 21:07.699
Mm, as was mine.

21:07.699 --> 21:09.034
Yes, well, it takes
a psychiatrist

21:09.034 --> 21:09.968
to interpret that play.

21:09.968 --> 21:12.704
Mm-hmm. Indeed.
All right, you go first.

21:12.704 --> 21:14.106
All right.
Go.

21:14.106 --> 21:15.607
"A descent into madness
proves well worth the trip

21:15.607 --> 21:18.110
in this incandescent revival
of A Streetcar Named Desire."

21:18.110 --> 21:19.111
Just a moment, Niles.
Incandescent--

21:19.111 --> 21:20.612
isn't that the same tired word

21:20.612 --> 21:22.114
you used
for that Saint Joan review?

21:22.114 --> 21:23.115
For God's sake...

